body_html:
I tested the patch on the 1.3 TAG v1.3.0-rc2 because I was doing performance tests with the various versions. With the env from the original post. The 1.3 final is not that different, you can look at the log but I am fairly sure it was a few small cherry picks. I am a bit surprised it did not apply. You can always apply to the TAG and then merge. If the merging does not get too messy you could merge all the way to head. Then make a branch, share it, and bask in some tasty karma. :-)

body:
I tested the patch on the 1.3 TAG v1.3.0-rc2 because I was doing
performance tests with the various versions.  With the env from the
original post.  The 1.3 final is not that different, you can look at the
log but I am fairly sure it was a few small cherry picks.  I am a bit
surprised it did not apply.  You can always apply to the TAG and then
merge.  If the merging does not get too messy you could merge all the way
to head.  Then make a branch, share it, and bask in some tasty karma.  :-)
